00:03:19.010 --> 00:03:20.990 align:middle line:90%
Why juice at the beginning?

00:03:20.990 --> 00:03:23.705 align:middle line:84%
This catalyst for you,
transforming your health

00:03:23.705 --> 00:03:25.580 align:middle line:84%
and the "Fat, Sick &
Nearly Dead" film, which

00:03:25.580 --> 00:03:27.978 align:middle line:90%
was just so transformative--

00:03:27.978 --> 00:03:30.020 align:middle line:84%
I know when people watch
it, they're so inspired.

00:03:30.020 --> 00:03:31.850 align:middle line:84%
But what was it about
juice in particular

00:03:31.850 --> 00:03:35.160 align:middle line:84%
that made you decide to
use that as a particular--

00:03:35.160 --> 00:03:40.030 align:middle line:90%
>> So I got to juice via plants.

00:03:40.030 --> 00:03:44.070 align:middle line:84%
The original concept was,
OK, I'm fat and I'm sick.

00:03:44.070 --> 00:03:46.100 align:middle line:90%
I need to fix this.

00:03:46.100 --> 00:03:48.740 align:middle line:84%
So I thought, I'll take
the sick one first.

00:03:48.740 --> 00:03:54.380 align:middle line:84%
And my turning my back on
Mother Nature, saying to her,

00:03:54.380 --> 00:03:55.980 align:middle line:90%
look, I'll be fine--

00:03:55.980 --> 00:03:57.830 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to go down
this processed route

00:03:57.830 --> 00:04:00.350 align:middle line:90%
and catch you later.

00:04:00.350 --> 00:04:04.170 align:middle line:84%
You cannot ignore the biological
laws of cause and effect.

00:04:04.170 --> 00:04:07.490 align:middle line:84%
You go and do that, you
will break eventually.

00:04:07.490 --> 00:04:10.140 align:middle line:90%
I broke at age 32.

00:04:10.140 --> 00:04:13.490 align:middle line:84%
And I couldn't
believe that I broke.

00:04:13.490 --> 00:04:14.450 align:middle line:90%
I'm a rugby player.

00:04:14.450 --> 00:04:15.250 align:middle line:90%
I'm strong.

00:04:15.250 --> 00:04:16.579 align:middle line:90%
I've always been fit.

00:04:16.579 --> 00:04:19.680 align:middle line:84%
And here I am taking meds
every day, every lunchtime,

00:04:19.680 --> 00:04:20.480 align:middle line:90%
every evening.

00:04:20.480 --> 00:04:21.529 align:middle line:84%
And the doctor's
saying, Joe, you're

00:04:21.529 --> 00:04:23.112 align:middle line:84%
going to be on this
for all your life.

00:04:23.112 --> 00:04:25.160 align:middle line:84%
And I'm like, I
don't think so, pal.

00:04:25.160 --> 00:04:28.480 align:middle line:84%
But then eight years later,
I'm still taking them.

00:04:28.480 --> 00:04:30.140 align:middle line:90%
And this was a disease of touch.

00:04:30.140 --> 00:04:31.670 align:middle line:90%
This was a bad illness.

00:04:31.670 --> 00:04:34.050 align:middle line:84%
So it's called chronic
urticaria angioedema.

00:04:34.050 --> 00:04:35.690 align:middle line:84%
It's fancy way of
saying chronic hives.

00:04:35.690 --> 00:04:38.060 align:middle line:84%
And if you and I shook
hands and you shook my hand

00:04:38.060 --> 00:04:40.970 align:middle line:84%
just a normal
tight grip, my hand

00:04:40.970 --> 00:04:43.670 align:middle line:84%
could swell up as though it
had been jammed in a car door.

00:04:43.670 --> 00:04:45.770 align:middle line:84%
That's the kind of pain
that I would go through

00:04:45.770 --> 00:04:48.800 align:middle line:84%
from any physical pressure,
any touch on my body.

00:04:48.800 --> 00:04:50.870 align:middle line:90%
So it was a big issue.

00:04:50.870 --> 00:04:54.350 align:middle line:84%
So when I decided to
consume only plant food,

00:04:54.350 --> 00:04:57.680 align:middle line:84%
to switch away from this
standard American diet

00:04:57.680 --> 00:04:59.450 align:middle line:84%
that I was consuming,
high processed

00:04:59.450 --> 00:05:02.030 align:middle line:84%
foods, high refined
sugars, carbohydrates,

00:05:02.030 --> 00:05:04.610 align:middle line:84%
lots of takeaway,
lots of alcohol,

00:05:04.610 --> 00:05:09.110 align:middle line:84%
smoking, no exercise,
this major stress,

00:05:09.110 --> 00:05:11.480 align:middle line:90%
all of these lifestyle choices--

00:05:11.480 --> 00:05:15.470 align:middle line:84%
when I decided to clean
house, the idea of plants

00:05:15.470 --> 00:05:16.560 align:middle line:90%
just made sense.

00:05:16.560 --> 00:05:17.390 align:middle line:90%
It's just logical.

00:05:17.390 --> 00:05:20.090 align:middle line:84%
Go back to what made us
the most successful species

00:05:20.090 --> 00:05:23.360 align:middle line:84%
on this planet, Mother
Nature, that partnership.

00:05:23.360 --> 00:05:24.930 align:middle line:90%
So that was the sick part.

00:05:24.930 --> 00:05:27.680 align:middle line:84%
But now when you go to
the fat part, James,

00:05:27.680 --> 00:05:32.010 align:middle line:84%
why was I carrying around an
extra 100 pounds or an extra 40

00:05:32.010 --> 00:05:33.600 align:middle line:90%
kilos of fat?

00:05:33.600 --> 00:05:35.300 align:middle line:90%
What was the purpose of it?

00:05:35.300 --> 00:05:37.140 align:middle line:84%
And when you go back
and look at this,

00:05:37.140 --> 00:05:39.790 align:middle line:84%
you realize it's just
stored up energy.

00:05:39.790 --> 00:05:41.915 align:middle line:84%
People walk around saying,
oh, how fat that person,

00:05:41.915 --> 00:05:43.500 align:middle line:84%
look at how fat--
they're not fat.

00:05:43.500 --> 00:05:45.810 align:middle line:84%
They're just people carrying
all this extra energy.

00:05:45.810 --> 00:05:49.020 align:middle line:84%
And their body is waiting
for that moment in time

00:05:49.020 --> 00:05:52.990 align:middle line:84%
when there's no energy consumed
so that energy can be used.

00:05:52.990 --> 00:05:58.230 align:middle line:84%
And so I thought, wow,
this is an aha moment here.

00:05:58.230 --> 00:05:59.860 align:middle line:90%
I need to not eat.

00:05:59.860 --> 00:06:02.610 align:middle line:84%
I need to go back to
what my ancestors did,

00:06:02.610 --> 00:06:05.220 align:middle line:84%
which is pretend that
there's a famine.

00:06:05.220 --> 00:06:06.720 align:middle line:84%
We've gone through
feast and famine.

00:06:06.720 --> 00:06:09.210 align:middle line:84%
That's part of the
history of our humanity.

00:06:09.210 --> 00:06:13.590 align:middle line:84%
And I have forgotten
how to famine.

00:06:13.590 --> 00:06:15.180 align:middle line:90%
So then I had this big problem.

00:06:15.180 --> 00:06:17.370 align:middle line:84%
I'm like, don't eat
and eat lots of plants.

00:06:17.370 --> 00:06:18.180 align:middle line:90%
I've got a problem.

00:06:18.180 --> 00:06:22.650 align:middle line:84%
I've got these two great
ideas, but they're not

00:06:22.650 --> 00:06:24.480 align:middle line:90%
coming together.

00:06:24.480 --> 00:06:25.740 align:middle line:90%
And then it hit me.

00:06:25.740 --> 00:06:27.450 align:middle line:90%
What is juicing?

00:06:27.450 --> 00:06:31.110 align:middle line:84%
Juicing is extracting
the water from plants.

00:06:31.110 --> 00:06:34.380 align:middle line:84%
It's not mashing up a
plant like a blender does.

00:06:34.380 --> 00:06:37.680 align:middle line:84%
It's actually stripping
out all of the water that

00:06:37.680 --> 00:06:39.450 align:middle line:90%
is harnessed in plants.

00:06:39.450 --> 00:06:43.950 align:middle line:84%
So when you put salary or
cucumber or an apple or kale

00:06:43.950 --> 00:06:45.630 align:middle line:90%
or a pear or ginger--

00:06:45.630 --> 00:06:47.490 align:middle line:84%
when you put that
through a juicer,

00:06:47.490 --> 00:06:49.110 align:middle line:90%
that's extracting the water out.

00:06:49.110 --> 00:06:52.230 align:middle line:84%
And the funny thing is it comes
in a colorful way, either red,

00:06:52.230 --> 00:06:54.340 align:middle line:84%
purple, green,
yellow, or orange.

00:06:54.340 --> 00:06:56.730 align:middle line:84%
You have five primary
colors of sunlight

00:06:56.730 --> 00:06:58.290 align:middle line:90%
that's harnessed in plants.

00:06:58.290 --> 00:07:01.500 align:middle line:84%
And that color is where
all those nutrients live,

00:07:01.500 --> 00:07:04.710 align:middle line:84%
these micronutrients,
these minerals,

00:07:04.710 --> 00:07:07.650 align:middle line:84%
these chemicals that
are absolutely critical

00:07:07.650 --> 00:07:13.710 align:middle line:84%
for our cell not only function,
but production and longevity.

00:07:13.710 --> 00:07:17.460 align:middle line:84%
And so if you think about
really what juice is,

00:07:17.460 --> 00:07:19.290 align:middle line:90%
it's the true Vitamin Water.

00:07:19.290 --> 00:07:21.510 align:middle line:90%
It's the true mineral water.

00:07:21.510 --> 00:07:23.880 align:middle line:90%
It's the true nutrient water.

00:07:23.880 --> 00:07:28.230 align:middle line:84%
And it's not eating, which
gave me that bit of leeway

00:07:28.230 --> 00:07:31.650 align:middle line:84%
I was trying to create
by the famine idea.

00:07:31.650 --> 00:07:34.837 align:middle line:84%
So I look at juice "fasting--"
and the word "fasting"

00:07:34.837 --> 00:07:37.170 align:middle line:84%
is the wrong word to use
there, but everyone understands

00:07:37.170 --> 00:07:40.560 align:middle line:84%
what that means, because
fasting is zero calories, zero

00:07:40.560 --> 00:07:41.730 align:middle line:90%
energy, zero nutrients.

00:07:41.730 --> 00:07:46.530 align:middle line:84%
But if we just give us a bit of
latitude and say juice fasting,

00:07:46.530 --> 00:07:49.170 align:middle line:84%
it really means you
are not consuming

00:07:49.170 --> 00:07:53.940 align:middle line:90%
any fiber that is insoluble.

00:07:53.940 --> 00:07:55.560 align:middle line:84%
You're only consuming
soluble fiber,

00:07:55.560 --> 00:07:59.220 align:middle line:84%
so fiber that can dissolve and
be so tiny it's in the water,

00:07:59.220 --> 00:08:02.700 align:middle line:84%
but the stuff that is
the mechanism that plants

00:08:02.700 --> 00:08:04.980 align:middle line:84%
have created to deliver
the nutrients to us.

00:08:04.980 --> 00:08:09.330 align:middle line:84%
That fiber when you eat celery,
James, you actually pass out

00:08:09.330 --> 00:08:10.740 align:middle line:90%
the fiber through your bowels.

00:08:10.740 --> 00:08:15.660 align:middle line:84%
You don't consume the fiber to
give you any nutrient benefit.

00:08:15.660 --> 00:08:18.210 align:middle line:90%
The nutrients are in the water.

00:08:18.210 --> 00:08:21.360 align:middle line:84%
They're trapped molecules
that are in the water that

00:08:21.360 --> 00:08:24.420 align:middle line:90%
are in the celery plant itself.

00:08:24.420 --> 00:08:26.192 align:middle line:90%
So the idea of juice--

00:08:26.192 --> 00:08:27.900 align:middle line:84%
I know I've given you
a long answer here.

00:08:27.900 --> 00:08:31.710 align:middle line:84%
But the idea for me is that it
was this beautiful combination

00:08:31.710 --> 00:08:34.140 align:middle line:84%
and magic of getting
the nutrients I need

00:08:34.140 --> 00:08:38.700 align:middle line:84%
from Mother Nature and providing
this, in inverted commas,

00:08:38.700 --> 00:08:39.630 align:middle line:90%
"fast."

00:08:39.630 --> 00:08:42.120 align:middle line:84%
So I was tricking my
body into thinking

00:08:42.120 --> 00:08:44.280 align:middle line:84%
it wasn't eating
when in actual fact,

00:08:44.280 --> 00:08:46.360 align:middle line:84%
I was flooding it
with micronutrients.

00:08:46.360 --> 00:08:47.160 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:08:47.160 --> 00:08:48.510 align:middle line:90%
It's so fascinating, isn't it?

00:08:48.510 --> 00:08:52.230 align:middle line:84%
Because we have
such a rich history

00:08:52.230 --> 00:08:53.550 align:middle line:90%
as humans on this planet.

00:08:53.550 --> 00:08:55.180 align:middle line:90%
And we've gone through so much.

00:08:55.180 --> 00:08:56.760 align:middle line:84%
And it's only been
in recent times

00:08:56.760 --> 00:08:59.760 align:middle line:84%
that we have seen
processed foods,

00:08:59.760 --> 00:09:02.893 align:middle line:84%
that we've seen preserved
foods, preserved incorrectly.

00:09:02.893 --> 00:09:05.310 align:middle line:84%
I'm not talking about fermented
foods, properly fermented.

00:09:05.310 --> 00:09:08.070 align:middle line:84%
I'm talking incorrectly
preserved and salted foods.

00:09:08.070 --> 00:09:10.710 align:middle line:84%
And it's caused such
havoc on our bodies.

00:09:10.710 --> 00:09:12.870 align:middle line:84%
And it makes so much
sense to just go back

00:09:12.870 --> 00:09:15.477 align:middle line:84%
towards these natural
processes of fasting.

00:09:15.477 --> 00:09:17.310 align:middle line:84%
You talked about the
difference a little bit

00:09:17.310 --> 00:09:18.727 align:middle line:84%
